oc:kn_20f7601d a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When issues are moved to In Progress status" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never skip linking PRs, commits, and docs to Linear issues. Issues without linked PRs after 48 hours should trigger reminders." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Unlinked work creates traceability gaps, making it impossible to audit what code changes relate to which requirements." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_2f4a452a a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning cycle/sprint scope" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Configure cycle planning with a 20% buffer and 8 points capacity per engineer per 2-week cycle. Do not overcommit beyond planned capacity." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Including buffer accounts for unplanned work and estimation inaccuracy, protecting team commitment and completion rates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_58d18e5c a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating or updating issues in Linear" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Follow the standard Linear issue lifecycle: Backlog → Todo → In Progress → In Review → Done. Each status transition should be intentional and automated where possible." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Consistent issue lifecycle tracking ensures team visibility, accurate velocity measurement, and predictable delivery workflows." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7ac82809 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring Linear workspace automations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Leverage automation triggers for status transitions: auto-assign on start, auto-add to cycle on sprint-ready label, auto-close on PR merge. Let integrations drive status updates rather than manual changes." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Automation reduces manual overhead, ensures consistent status hygiene, and keeps the team focused on actual work rather than ticket management." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_83f783ff a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating new issues in Linear" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use structured issue templates (Bug Report, Feature Request, Epic Breakdown) with consistent labeling and required fields. Always include acceptance criteria for features and reproduction steps for bugs." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Standardized templates reduce ambiguity, speed up triage, and ensure no critical information is missing from issues." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_dcb521fe a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When executing automated issue creation workflows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Issue creation and updates are not idempotent by default. Re-running a create operation will produce duplicate issues unless guarded by duplicate detection logic." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Duplicate issues create confusion in backlog grooming and inflate velocity metrics, so workflows should check for existing issues before creating." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

